'''乔治·罗斯·伊哈卡'''（'''George Ross Ihaka'''，{{bd|1954年||||catIdx=I}}）<ref name=nzh>{{cite web|url=//www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10551243|title=Academic unfazed by rock star status|newspaper=[[New_Zealand_Herald|New Zealand Herald]]|date=2009-01-10|accessdate=2020-09-16|archive-date=2009-07-13|archive-url=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090713215059/http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=10551243|dead-url=no}}</ref>在[[奥克兰大学|奥克兰大学]]统计系任副教授。 伊哈卡与[[罗伯特·杰特曼|罗伯特·杰特曼]]是[[R语言|R语言]]的最初作者。<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Ihaka | first1 = R. | last2 = Gentleman | first2 = R. | title = R: A Language for Data Analysis and Graphics | journal = Journal of Computational and Graphical Statistics | volume = 5 | issue = 3 | pages = 299–314 | doi = 10.2307/1390807 | year = 1996 | jstor = 1390807| pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Data Analysts Captivated by R's Power | url=//www.nytimes.com/2009/01/07/technology/business-computing/07program.html|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2009-01-07 | first=Ashlee | last=Vance | date=2009-01-07}}</ref>  

伊哈卡在1985年从[[加州大学伯克利分校|加州大学伯克利分校]]获得博士学位，其导师是戴维·R·布勒林格。<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.stat.berkeley.edu/~brill/students.html| title=David's students| accessdate=2014-08-14| website=stat.berkeley.edu | publisher=Department of Statistics, University of California, Berkeley}}</ref> 2008年新西兰皇家科学院向伊哈卡颁发皮克林勋章以纪念其对R语言的贡献。<ref>[http://www.royalsociety.org.nz/programmes/awards/pickering-medal/recipients/ Pickering Medal: Recipients], Royal Society of New Zealand.</ref>截止至2010年，伊哈卡正在编写一种基于[[LISP|LISP]]的统计编程语言。<ref>{{cite conference|title=Back to the Future: Lisp as a Base for a Statistical Computing System|first1=Ross|last1=Ihaka|first2=Duncan|last2=Temple Lang|date=2008-08-25|conference=Compstat 2008|url=//www.stat.auckland.ac.nz/%7Eihaka/downloads/Compstat-2008.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{cite conference|title=R: Lessons Learned, Directions for the Future|first=Ross|last=Ihaka| url=//www.stat.auckland.ac.nz/%7Eihaka/downloads/JSM-2010.pdf|conference=Joint Statistical Meetings 2010, Statistical Computing Section|date=2010}}</ref>

